sql:
SELECT value
FROM gfl_index
WHERE indicator = '12.3.1' AND geo_area_code = 1 AND time_period = 1;

SELECT AVG(value) AS average_gfl_index
FROM gfl_index
WHERE geo_area_name = 'Europe and Northern America' AND time_period = 2016;

external_knowledge:
- "GFLI" stands for Global Financial Literacy Index;
- "Most recent three entries" refers to the latest three time periods for each geographic area;
- "Indicator code" is a unique identifier for the GFLI;
- "Series description" provides a brief description of the series of data;
- "Geographic area name" is the name of the region or country;
- "Time period" refers to the specific year or quarter for which the data is recorded;
- "Value" is the numerical value of the GFLI for the given time period.

